    <statement>
      <p>
        Do the following division problems without using a calculator.
        a)    <m>\displaystyle<var name="$a1" /> \div <var name="$b1" /> =</m>  <var name="$ans1" width="8" />
        b)    <m>\displaystyle<var name="$a2" /> \div <var name="$b2" /> =</m>  <var name="$ans2" width="8" />
      </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
      <p>
        *Part 1:* When the number being divided has trailing zeroes, we can ignore them, do the division, and then add back those zeroes.
      </p>

      <p>
        <m><var name="$a1" /></m> has <m><var name="$a1Exp" /></m> trailing <var name="$zeroText1" />. We can ignore <var name="$itOrThem" />, and simply do <m><var name="$a" />\div<var name="$b" />=[$a/$b]</m> first.
      </p>

      <p>
        Then, we add back <m><var name="$a1Exp" /></m> <var name="$zeroText1" />, and the answer is <m><var name="$a1" />\div<var name="$b1" />=<var name="$ans1" /></m>.
      </p>

      <p>
        *Part 2:* When we do division of numbers with trailing zeroes, we can cross out the same number of zeroes from those two numbers, and then do the division.
      </p>

      <p>
        <m><var name="$a2" /></m> has <m><var name="$a2Exp" /></m> trailing zeroes, and <m><var name="$b2" /></m> has <m><var name="$b2Exp" /></m> trailing <var name="$zeroText2" />. We will cross out <m><var name="$b2Exp" /></m> trailing <var name="$zeroText2" />, and do:
      </p>

      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow><var name="$a2" />\div<var name="$b2" /> \amp= <var name="$s1" /> \div <var name="$s2" /></mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= <var name="$ans2" /></mrow>
        </md>
      </p>

      <p>
        *More Explanations of Part 1:* First, we need to understand that division and fraction line are the same operation. For example, <m>6 \div 2 = 3</m>, while <m>\frac{6}{2}=3</m>.
      </p>

      <p>
        The number <m><var name="$a1" /></m> can be viewed as <m><var name="$a" />\cdot<var name="$s3" /></m>. When we do <m><var name="$a1" />\div<var name="$b1" /></m>, we can do:
      </p>

      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow><var name="$a1" />\div<var name="$b1" /> \amp= \frac{<var name="$a1" />}{<var name="$b1" />}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= \frac{<var name="$a" /> \cdot <var name="$s3" />}{<var name="$b1" />}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= \frac{<var name="$a" />}{<var name="$b1" />} \cdot <var name="$s3" /></mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= <var name="$s4" /> \cdot <var name="$s3" /></mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= <var name="$ans1" /></mrow>
        </md>
      </p>

      <p>
        *More Explanations of Part 2:*
      </p>

      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow><var name="$a2" />\div<var name="$b2" /> \amp= \frac{<var name="$a2" />}{<var name="$b2" />}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= \frac{<var name="$a" /> \cdot <var name="$s5" />}{<var name="$b" /> \cdot <var name="$s6" />}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= \frac{<var name="$a" />}{<var name="$b" />} \cdot \frac{<var name="$s5" />}{<var name="$s6" />}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= <var name="$s4" /> \cdot <var name="$s7" /></mrow>
          <mrow>\amp= <var name="$ans2" /></mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </solution>
